<br>
Yes, I can and I did read the screenshots in your first post.  I can also make a convincing argument out of those that you're the one harassing Imasu.<br>
<br>
Looking at what's on the table, I don't see the substance of your complaint.  He tells his guild not to deal with this person--I'd think this would be what you wanted, since that would mean they wouldn't be speaking to her, much less &quot;harassing&quot; her.  Perhaps I'm confused.  Do you mean to imply that not talking to someone is also a form of harassment?<br>
<br>
Regardless (&quot;irregardless&quot; isn't a word, by the way), this seems to also offend you because he's &quot;policing&quot; his guild.  I'm not sure where you think you have standing to complain about that.  Instructions given to the guild are between the guild and its leader.  You're not a party to that, so it is really none of your business.<br>
<br>
